post_text:
Today is 5 meal Friday at secondary sites, pick up your grab and go meals at your closest secondary site. Or you can pick up one day worth of meals at your local elementary school.

We have also moved to a new program as long as funding lasts to provide free meals to all children 18 years and younger at our school sites.

Meal Applications still should be completed for the 2020/2021 school year as meal applications impact school funding. meal applications and additional information can be found at www.ausdnutrition.org Thank you and please thank the team's feeding our families as we continue to get through this together.

Presented by our Coordinator of Mental Health, the webinar will discuss responses to trauma and how to build a more resilient you, so that you can build resilience within your child.

If you would like to have a question addressed during the webinar, please submit it to https://tinyurl.com/AUSDResilience

post_text: Dr. Tania Cabeza was named as the new principal of La Sierra High School on 4.27.20. She comes to AUSD from Centinela Valley UHSD. post_text: In his press conference today (at the 52-minute mark) Governor Newsom discussed what schools may look like in the fall knowing that mass gatherings will be "negligible at best," even into the fall months. He talked about staggering the school day to optimize space and increase the likelihood that social distancing practices can still be followed. Lots can change between now and Fall, 2020, but it's important that you know that Alvord and all districts will be considering different ways to deliver in-person learning once schools are cleared to open. Find the press conference here: https://www.facebook.com/CAgovernor/videos/519465758996288/

post_text:
Vaping: The Facts

Nicotine is highly addictive and can harm brain development which continues until age 25. In addition to nicotine, some cartridges contain marijuana which often comes in the form of concentrated cannabis, synthetic cannabis or wax. The liquid or ‚Äújuice‚Äù comes in over 7,000 flavors with names that cater to the younger generation. The flavors mask the harsh taste of tobacco which makes it easier for kids to smoke. Four out of five kids who have used tobacco started with a flavored product. E-cigarettes are known by many names: ‚Äúe-cigs,‚Äù ‚Äúmods,‚Äù ‚Äúvape pens,‚Äù ‚Äúvapes,‚Äù and electronic nicotine delivery systems.
